Audi will have to modify up to 850,000 diesel cars
The day before the Audi announcement, BMW said it would offer to update the software to more than 350,000 vehicles.
The Chairman of BMW said that the company believes that “there are more intelligent ways than driving restrictions”, referring to European cities – including Munich, where BMW is located – which considered the possibility of banning or limiting the use of diesel cars.
Daimler said on Thursday it would modify three million Mercedes-Benz vehicles in Europe to reduce their diesel emissions.
None of the companies called their move a recall.
European automakers have actively promoted the use of diesel cars in Europe and the United States to promote compliance with carbon rules.
But the nitrogen oxides that diesel engines emit are considered carcinogens and can cause asthma.
