One of their journalists learned from open databases that the restaurant was registered in the name of a politician belonging to the ruling Institutional Revolutionary Party (PRI), which has dominated all levels of government for almost the past century.
Recently, several governors from PRI have been accused of corruption.
Villarreal asked reporters to write about previous incidents at the restaurant, including when El Chapo’s son Guzman slipped away from a military raid.
