Electricity is cheaper for both residents and producers of Buryatia
The efforts of the Soviet and post-Soviet authorities of the Republic of Buryatia (Eastern Siberia) to establish fair tariffs for electricity consumers are beginning to bear fruit.
From September 1, the cost of low-voltage electricity for industrial recipients is reduced by 25%.
The Federal Antimonopoly Service of the country in accordance with the Decree of the Government of the Russian Federation "On Amendments to the Rules of the Wholesale Market of Electricity and Power and to the Consolidated Forecast Balance of Production and Supply of Electricity (Power) within the Unified Energy System of Russia by Subjects of the Russian Federation" (from 17.07.2017 No. 842) has established indicative prices for electricity and power by the Buryats of the Republic.
As a result, the cost of electricity for Buryat commodity producers is reduced by a quarter, which will greatly facilitate the life of small and medium-sized enterprises and individual entrepreneurs.
For many decades, the leaders of the republic beat the thresholds of the Moscow cabinets in vain attempts to level the region in tariffs with the neighboring Irkutsk region with a cascade of hydroelectric power plants on the Angara, flowing from Baikal, the main catchment area for which is Buryatia.
It was only this year that the movement began.
In March, electricity tariffs for the population of the republic were reduced from 4.24 rubles/kWh to 3.93 rubles/kWh, or by 7.3%.
With the inclusion of Buryatia by the decision of the federal government in the List of territories of the price zones of the wholesale market, for which the features of the functioning of the wholesale and retail markets are established, the turn of industrial consumers has come.
According to analysts, this is only the beginning, since the population of the Irkutsk region pays for a kilowatt / hour of 1.01 rubles.
But no one dares to name at least an approximate date of new tariff moves towards a decrease for Buryatia.
